<TITLE>Montgomery Internship Program -- MRC</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<blockquote>
<center><h1>MRC Montgomery Internships Available</h1></center>
<center><h3>Now Accepting Resumes!</h3></center>
<P>
<P>
	The Media Research Center has paid internships available for conservatives interested in studying the media's impact on American society.<BR>

<P>
     	MRC Montgomery Internships are available throughout the academic year and summer.  Prospective applicants must be knowledgeable about conservative political issues, the news and/or entertainment industries, and possess strong writing skills. <BR>

<P>
     	Responsibilities include monitoring news or entertainment television shows, researching magazines and newspapers, assisting with various research projects, and writing newsletter copy. <BR>

<P>
	The MRC is located just outside of Washington, DC in historic Old Town Alexandria, Virginia, within walking distance of the King Street Metro station. <BR>

<P>
	Please fill out the attached <a href="/mrc/about/internship.html">application</a> or send a resume and writing sample to Christine Brookhart at the Media Research Center, 113 South West Street, 2nd Floor, Alexandria, VA, 22314; fax to (703)683-9736; or email to cbrookhart@mediaresearch.org.

