<title>Web Developers and Internships</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<h2><center>Web Developers and Interns Needed</center></h2>

<center><h3>Winter/Spring Interns</h3></center>
<blockquote>
Town Hall is looking for full and part-time interns to assist the Producer in illustration, layout and design of Web sites. Interns will also assist in Marketing, Advertising sales, and Administration responsibilities. Must have facility with PC's and Windows. HTML a plus. $6. per hour, up to $250. per week. Internships typically last 3-4 months starting in January and lasting till mid-May. Interns will also participate in the Heritage Foundation's Lectures and Seminars program, often seen on C-SPAN. 
<p>
<h3><center>Web Developers</center></h3>

Town Hall is looking for an entry-level web developer to assist the Producer in layout, design and backend implementation of Web sites. Must have experience using computers and the internet. HTML and UNIX experience preferred. Perl, Java and/or Javascript a plus. Salary plus excellent benefits. 
<p>
Interested Applicants must prepare a brief statement containing the following:<p>
<ul>
<li>Why you wish to work/intern at Town Hall?
<li>What political/cultural issue is most important to you and what you would like to seen done?
<li>What aspect of Town Hall should be developed more to better utilitize the new medium of communication?
</ul>

Applicant should send Resume, Cover letter, Statement, and Political/Professional/Educational references to:<p>

