<a href="/thcc/content/bozell/boze011397.html"><img src="/thcc/images/bozell.gif" border="0" align="left" alt="L. Brent Bozell">
<b>TEN REASONS ETHICS NEWS REEKS OF BIAS</b></a><br>

Reporters would have you believe the news media's non-stop coverage of the Newt Gingrich ethics story is standard operating
     procedure. No agenda, no bias, no sirree. Let this writer give you 10 reasons why that is bunk, why this is anything but standard
     coverage of congressional ethics.
<p><br>

<a href="/thcc/content/feder/fede011397.html"><img src="/thcc/images/feder.gif" border="0" align="right" alt="Don Feder">
<b>THE ROGHT-TO-DIE?</b></a><br>

In oral arguments on physician-assisted suicide last week, justices of the Supreme Court showed merciful restraint and
     unaccustomed awareness of where the formulation of new rights can lead.
<p><br>

<a href="/thcc/content/novak/nova011397.html"><img src="/thcc/images/novak.gif" border="0" align="left" alt="ROBERT D. NOVAK">
<b>INSIDE REPORT</b></a><br>

 In contrast to his contrite acceptance speech after re- election as speaker of the House, Newt Gingrich was
     his hard-nosed old self in pleading his case to a closed-door conference of House Republicans before the vote.
<p><br>

<a href="/thcc/content/quayle/quay011397.html"><img src="/thcc/images/quayle.gif" border="0" align="right" alt="DAN QUAYLE">
<b>GROWTH</b></a><br>

While President Clinton often boasts of a "growing economy," he rarely mentions the rate of growth, which in recent years has
     been anemic in comparison to other postwar recoveries.
<p><br>

<a href="/thcc/content/saunders/saun011397.html"><img src="/thcc/images/saunders.gif" border="0" align="left" alt="DEBRA J. SAUNDERS">
<b>WILSON'S EDUCATION PLAN</b></a><br>

Last year, when Gov. Pete Wilson announced his plan to spend more than $771 million to reduce class size in early
     elementary school grades, some educators privately believed that the reduction was not a wise use of taxpayer money. I kept
     quiet.
<p><br>

<a href="/thcc/content/sowell/sowe011397.html"><img src="/thcc/images/sowell.gif" border="0" align="right" alt="THOMAS SOWELL">
<b>COLLEGES VERSUS EDUCATION</b></a><br>

Over the past several years, study after study has brought the painful news of how ignorant our high school graduates -- and even
     graduates of Ivy League colleges -- are of things that were once considered basic. 
<p><br>



